Scenario:
A developer says:
“It works on my machine but not on the server.”
You are asked to containerize the app.
Explain:
Why Docker reduces this issue
What still can go wrong even with Docker
What you would verify before blaming Docker

Solution :-
Why Docker Reduces This

Because:

Same image runs everywhere

Same dependencies

Same OS libraries

Same runtime

Immutable build

Environment becomes reproducible.

What Can Still Go Wrong

Different CPU architecture (arm64 vs amd64)

Wrong environment variables

Volume mount path differences

File permission issues

Network/firewall restrictions

SELinux/AppArmor blocking

Docker version mismatch

Kernel incompatibility

Docker reduces problems — does NOT eliminate all.

What I Would Verify

docker version

docker info

CPU architecture

Environment variables

Port mapping

Volume mounts

Logs

Kernel version
